race.comment: A tough way to finish. HEADLINE LEGEND (15) may sit closer today and his narrow defeat at Toowoomba three starts ago in a CL3 stacks right up. Plain since but suited better at this level with a 1.5kg claim. HIGH SECURITY (3) resumed at Dalby and lost the rider. Was well in commission and sis good enough to fight out the finish with average luck in the run. The yard is flying. SWEETPEA MOOCHI (7) rates well enough on his 1L defeat in a 58 at Glen Innes two back. That would see him competitive in this lineup. PACIFIC PIRATE (13) resumed at Dalby and didn't have the best of luck. He raced well at his only start at this track and jumps from an inside barrier. Fitter and is also in the mix.
